title: Grateful Dead Live at Harding Theater on 1971-11-07
description:
Set 1

Truckin', Brown Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, Hideaway, Sugaree, Jack Straw, Tennessee Jed, Cumberland Blues, El Paso, Big Railroad Blues, Comes A Time, Mexicali Blues, One More Saturday Night

Set 2

Ramble On Rose, Me And Bobby McGee, Loser, Sugar Magnolia, Dark Star-> Drums-> The Other One-> Me & My Uncle-> The Other One, Deal, Brokedown Palace, Playin' In The Band, Casey Jones, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: Johnny B. Goode, E: Uncle John's Band

*FM broadcast KSFX-San FrancLsco - Other artist(s): NRPS

reviews.review_text: Finally! What a great Christmas gift. This is a huge improvement over all other versions. I always had hope since the "Taper's Section" once played the Dark Star and it sounded flawless. No point in reviewing the show itself as we all know how good it is, but if you randomly check by your list of favorites for upgrades...This is IT! A big thanks to the responsible parties.
